\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all Information Operations Department personnel participating in incident response operations during the eradication phase.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Compliance with this policy shall be assessed through the ECIO internal audit program governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Internal Audits,
 Self-Assessment,
 and Control Testing) and the annual policy review and maturity scoring process governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 The following conditions constitute specific non-compliance with this policy:
 initiation of eradication activity before the Incident Commander has documented a containment-complete determination under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
;
 execution of destructive or irreversible eradication actions without prior IC authorization or without documented confirmation that forensic preservation requirements have been satisfied;
 execution of eradication actions that deviate from the IC-selected eradication procedures without documented IC authorization;
 execution of eradication actions without an associated work order in the System of Engagement;
 failure to create catch-up RFC documentation within the twenty-four (24) hour window established by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
;
 any eradication action that destroys,
 overwrites,
 or causes the disposition of audit logs maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Audit Logging and Monitoring Policy) or forensic evidence without documented IC authorization and justification;
 and failure to document an eradication-complete determination in the work order Notes before initiating recovery activity under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Non-compliance may result in corrective action in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy require written approval from the IT Director in accordance with the exception management framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 No open-ended exceptions are permitted.
 All approved exceptions shall be documented and time-bounded.
 No exception shall authorize the destruction,
 overwriting,
 or untracked disposition of preserved evidence,
 required audit records,
 or mandatory incident-record documentation.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
\end_layout

