\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.4 Eradication-Complete Determination
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Eradication is complete when the threat has been fully neutralized —
 all identified threat actors,
 malicious artifacts,
 compromised configurations,
 persistence mechanisms,
 and exploited vulnerabilities have been removed or remediated across all systems within the containment perimeter.
 No phase transition is assumed.
 The IC shall make an explicit eradication-complete determination,
 documented in the work order Notes and Chapter 4 checklist,
 before any recovery activity under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 begins.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The following verification conditions are required for every eradication-complete determination.
 These conditions are necessary but explicitly not sufficient.
 The IC shall confirm that all scenario-specific verification criteria identified in the applicable eradication procedures have also been satisfied and shall document the basis for that confirmation in the work order Notes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The assigned technician shall verify all systems within the containment perimeter as clean using an authorized detection or validation method defined in the applicable eradication procedure.
 Where automated scanning is supported,
 a clean scan result from the Department's authorized scanning tools is required.
 Where automated scanning is not supported for a given system type,
 the applicable eradication procedure shall define the alternative validation method.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The assigned technician shall rotate,
 revoke,
 or replace all identified compromised credentials.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The assigned technician shall remove all identified persistence mechanisms,
 including unauthorized services,
 scheduled tasks,
 registry modifications,
 startup items,
 and unauthorized user accounts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The assigned technician shall patch all identified exploited vulnerabilities or implement documented compensating controls approved by the IC.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The assigned technician shall update CI records for all eradication-driven configuration changes per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 or confirm that pending CI updates are within the applicable documentation window with assigned owners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The assigned technician shall complete all catch-up RFC documentation for eradication-phase Emergency Changes,
 or confirm that pending RFC items are within the twenty-four (24) hour documentation window with assigned owners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IC shall document the eradication-complete determination with explicit reference to each mandatory verification condition and shall identify the eradication procedures that were invoked along with confirmation that their scenario-specific verification criteria were satisfied.
\end_layout

